title: 820-4924 no keyboard, no trackpad
message:
With new keyboard/trackpad/trackpad cable same story.

Keyboard connector:
PP3V3_S4 = 3.42V
PP3V42_G3H = 3.32V

Trackpad connector:
PPVIN_S4_TPAD_FUSE = 13V
PP3V3_S4_TPAD = 3.32V

title: 820-4924 no keyboard, no trackpad
message: Is the trackpad/keyboard listed in OSX under USB devices?

title: 820-4924 no keyboard, no trackpad
message: no, they are not listed there

title: 820-4924 no keyboard, no trackpad
message:
Sorry, this one will be listed under SPI devices, can you check again? Was this liquid damage?
Also check if it works when you are in the boot menu, hold down ALT key when turning on.

title: 820-4924 no keyboard, no trackpad
message:
No Title

No problem Duke.
No devices under SPI.
ALT not works during boot (on ext USB keyboard works fine)
There is just one small liquid marks like on photo bellow (no other signs of liquid).

title: 820-4924 no keyboard, no trackpad
message: Have you taken the board out and inspected everything, trackpad connector first of course. Does the trackpad click when powered on? These force touch ones don't click without power.

title: 820-4924 no keyboard, no trackpad
message:
Yes, I removed board and checked the other side and rest looks good.

There is a click on trackpad (single, not double as normal force touch).

title: 820-4924 no keyboard, no trackpad
message: So there is no click when off and there is a click when on? Have you swapped a known good trackpad and cable together?
